pageContext.claim: “I heard great things about the healthcare plan. And a lot of people are signing up; a lot of associations are signing up -- far ahead of what we even projected. So that's good.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump’s Labor Department has adopted a new rule to allow small businesses to band together to buy health-care plans as long as they share a “common geography or industry.” The Congressional Budget Office estimates that millions of people may switch over to these health plans, but there’s no evidence “millions of people are already signing up.” These plans won't be sold until September, and it's not clear that anyone has signed up for them.
